      "writtenOn": "2017-07-25T04:15:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I haven\u0027t been able to find a great way so far. I looked into the cutime and cstime fields in the stat file, which are supposed to be user/system cpu times for \"waited-for children\", but based on some experiments, they don\u0027t seem to include join-ed sibling threads.\n\nIs supplying wrappers to create some in-process bookkeeping an option? We could supply pthread_create/join routines for clients which record thread stats in a known place.",
